<?xml version="1.0" encoding="utf-8"?>
<androidx.constraintlayout.widget.ConstraintLayout xmlns:android="http://schemas.android.com/apk/res/android"
    android:layout_width="match_parent"
    android:layout_height="match_parent">

    <ScrollView
        android:layout_width="match_parent"
        android:layout_height="match_parent"
        android:padding="16dp">

        <LinearLayout
            android:layout_width="match_parent"
            android:layout_height="wrap_content"
            android:orientation="vertical">

            <TextView
                android:layout_width="wrap_content"
                android:layout_height="wrap_content"
                android:text="Game Rules :)"
                android:textAlignment="center"
                android:textSize="36sp"
                android:layout_marginBottom="16dp"/>

            <TextView
                android:layout_width="wrap_content"
                android:layout_height="wrap_content"
                android:text="1. Your sprite starts at 250 units."
                android:textSize="13sp"
                android:layout_marginBottom="12dp"/>

            <TextView
                android:layout_width="wrap_content"
                android:layout_height="wrap_content"
                android:textSize="13sp"
                android:text="2. When your character hits the same color circle as its background, it will grow by 10 units."
                android:layout_marginBottom="12dp"/>

            <TextView
                android:layout_width="wrap_content"
                android:layout_height="wrap_content"
                android:textSize="13sp"
                android:text="3. Conversely, when you character hits the wrong color circle, it will shrink by 5 units."
                android:layout_marginBottom="12dp"/>

            <TextView
                android:layout_width="wrap_content"
                android:layout_height="wrap_content"
                android:textSize="13sp"
                android:text="4. One of the circles can respawn at a random location once you click on it."
                android:layout_marginBottom="16dp"/>
            <TextView
                android:layout_width="wrap_content"
                android:layout_height="wrap_content"
                android:textSize="13sp"
                android:text="5. You will be able to change the color of your sprite (your character on the screen) based
based on your choice through 2 checkboxes, labeled Red and Green"
                android:layout_marginBottom="16dp"/>
            <TextView
                android:layout_width="wrap_content"
                android:layout_height="wrap_content"
                android:textSize="13sp"
                android:text="6. If the Red Checkbox is checked, the sprite will change to red. However if both checkboxes are selected, the color of you sprite will change to yellow, a combination of both colors."
                android:layout_marginBottom="16dp"/>
            <TextView
                android:layout_width="wrap_content"
                android:layout_height="wrap_content"
                android:textSize="13sp"
                android:text="7. Similar, selecting the Green checkbox will change the color of your sprite to green. If both
are checked, your sprite will turn yellow."
                android:layout_marginBottom="16dp"/>

            <TextView
                android:layout_width="wrap_content"
                android:layout_height="wrap_content"
                android:textSize="13sp"
                android:text="8. Similar, selecting the Green checkbox will change the color of your sprite to green. If both
are checked, your sprite will turn yellow."
                android:layout_marginBottom="16dp"/>

            <TextView
                android:layout_width="wrap_content"
                android:layout_height="wrap_content"
                android:textSize="12sp"
                android:text="9. If you uncheck both boxes, the sprite will turn blue."
                android:layout_marginBottom="16dp"/>

            <TextView
                android:layout_width="wrap_content"
                android:layout_height="wrap_content"
                android:textSize="12sp"
                android:text="10. In summary, matching colors increase size, non-matching colors decrease size. You want to get the
maximize your score."
                android:layout_marginBottom="12dp"/>

            <Button
                android:id="@+id/btnBackToMain"
                android:layout_width="wrap_content"
                android:layout_height="wrap_content"
                android:text="Start"
                android:layout_gravity="center_horizontal"/>

        </LinearLayout>
    </ScrollView>
</androidx.constraintlayout.widget.ConstraintLayout>